  "description": "This dataset comprises intracranial EEG recordings from patients during non-REM sleep, designed to support comprehensive modeling of high-frequency activity (part 1 of a multi-part study). The data were collected across multiple institutions including Wayne State University, Tohoku University, and the National Center of Neurology and Psychiatry, and represent part of a larger investigation into neural dynamics during sleep using invasive electrophysiological monitoring.",
